title: For Sale/Trade:  Armory USA AK $600 OBO
postcontent:
Due to the fact that I need a handgun and my AK doesn't quite have a role in my arsenal I figure its time to put it up for sale or for trade.

I've put maybe 1000 rounds through it and its a great gun. When I got it it had this horrible mismatched plastic furniture on it which I tolerated for about a month before I switched it out for some bringback furniture. I personally think that AK's should have wooden furniture, and this stuff is great. 
Couple notations about the gun: 
1-It is a bit magazine picky when it comes to steel surplus ones. I had 5 that I ended up giving away with my old WASR (I sold that after I got this) because they wouldn't fit it. Tapco polymer mags seem to fit just fine (I have one steel that fits and to tapcos). 
2-It has a chrome lined RPK barrel, RPK rear sight (adjustable for windage), and the reciever is made from RPK tooling and specs (its 1.5mm thick metal instead of 1mm like standard AK's). This means its more durable, accurate, and a bit heavier than your standard AK.  
3-From what the previous owner told me (I never messed with it) the muzzle threads are AR15/10 threads, so you can use AR-10 muzzle devices on it. I don't know if you would want to change the brake, but if you do thats some info you probably would want. 

The gun comes with 3 mags, 60 rounds of ammo, sling, a whole spare set of bringback furniture (butt stock, foregrip handguards, 2 handgrips), and a magpul handgrip (its what came on the gun and I like it so I kept it on there)

I've shot quite a few AK's and owned a WASR before this and this one is by far my favorite. Its very accurate, fun to shoot, and the little extra weight really helps to soften the recoil in the best way. Its a great gun and I would love to keep it, but I really really need a handgun. Please message me on here for trade offers (see below) or for cash offers

title: For Sale:  20" AR15 A1/pencil profile 1/7 twist 2MOA dot and 15" rail.
postcontent:
Barrel is a super hard to find 20" Vietnam era A1 pencil profile with a modern 1/7 twist and nitrocarburizing (harder than chrome).  Muzzle device is a 'type 89' dual chamber brake, same as used by the Japanese special forces by repute.  Standard PSA carpenter steel BCG and milspec charging handle.  Very light 15" keymod rail with BCM ergo hand stop, includes 1 long and 1 short aluminum rail sections.  Adjustable gas block includes 20-cycle hi-temp anti-seize and is tuned to eject in a neat pile at 4o'clock with a standard carbine buffer and spring. 

Optic is a Primary Arms 2moa dot.  Super clear dot even in bright AZ sun, and NV compatible.  Comparable to a trs-25 or similar entry level red dot; however the PA units have a much tighter dot and this one in particular has none of that 'galaxy' effect you find on budget units.  Magpul PTS BUIS included, spend $100+ on real ones if you feel strongly about it, irons are a very personal choice.

Lower is forged milspec all around with a PSA kit.  Trigger is actually surprisingly good for stock milspec. MFT BattleLink 6oz stock has great feel in pocket and no shake.

This is my personal rifle, built for self defense and hunting with a clear goal of light weight to facilitate extended carry/hiking.  Complete with optic this 20" AR weighs only 6.7lbs, which is less than most carbine barreled flat top rifles.  With the full length barrel, standard milsurp ammo retains enough energy to fragment out to 190+ yards.  It has around 150 rounds through it and operates flawlessly.

Includes 2 aluminum GI mags and 60 rounds of SS109 ammunition.  Also included are hex and star wrenches along with the gas block adjusting wrench.

Selling to fund a motorcycle purchase.  Price is 'obo' but firm as this is an uncommon and high quality rifle.  *EDIT* I've updated the optic to a more familiar model and changed the price to better reflect other nice rifles on GunBroker and Armslist.

Would happily direct trade for a good running motorcycle.  Ideally an e-start capable dual sport 400cc+ but shoot me an offer, a clean road bike would be fun too.
